## Adaptation Notes

### Board target

Confirm the actual MCU before building. Classic ESP32, ESP32-S3, and ESP32-C3 do not share the same target.

### USB port

If the board is not on `COM5`, change only the script argument:

```powershell
.\scripts\zclaw-flash.ps1 -Target esp32 -Port COM7
```

### AI provider changes

Keep the setup UI split between Wi-Fi and AI settings. If you support another OpenAI-compatible provider, normalize the base URL inside firmware instead of requiring the full endpoint from users.

### Sensor changes

This branch assumes DHT11 on `GPIO5`. If you move the pin or switch sensor family, retest both the direct local read path and the chat-triggered tool path.

### OLED changes

The physical display UI is tuned for a very small `128x32` screen. Keep text short, keep page count low, and retest layout if you move to `128x64` or another controller.

### Upstream zclaw updates

Expect merge pressure in:

- `main.c`
- `web_ui.c`
- `llm.c`
- `agent.c`
- sensor files
- OLED files

When updating upstream, keep the branch goals intact:

- AP provisioning
- local mobile chat
- SSE streaming
- DHT11 tool support
- OLED-guided setup

## Local Secrets

Keep local secrets out of Git. This branch intentionally ignores:

- `.zclaw_web_api_key`

Do not commit live Wi-Fi credentials or API keys.

## Branch Intent

This branch is meant to remain a long-lived `zclaw` integration branch, not a short-lived PR branch.
